The article is a letter addressed to the Speaker of the House, requesting Congress to consider amendments to the Fiscal Year (FY) 2022 Budget for various departments and agencies, including Agriculture, Defense, Education, Health and Human Services, Homeland Security, Housing and Urban Development, Justice, Labor, State, the District of Columbia, and the United States Agency for International Development. These amendments are necessary to accurately reflect the policies assumed in the FY 2022 Budget. The amendments would result in a $5 million increase in net discretionary budget authority. The details of the amendments are provided in a letter from the Acting Director of the Office of Management and Budget. The letter is signed by Joseph R. Biden Jr.